    <text id="B1244T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>An unspecified group of church members write on behalf of Emily Rodney, who was
                    prevented from holding religious meetings by Frederick Tukey.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1866-03-29">March 29th 66.</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, Virginia</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>we will inform you that <orig reg="it">its</orig> is a false report raise on
                    Sister Rodney she did not Tell any of the members of the Church to leave and
                    come to her <orig reg="meeting">meetting</orig>. we left because the <orig
                        reg="majority">majoyity</orig> of us went and give our Names to that
                    Conferences those oppose her and Brought the charge <orig reg="against"
                    >Againts</orig> her Mr Tukey heard speak and Her witness was silence and was Not
                        <orig reg="allowed">allowd</orig> to speak for her</p>

                <p>Why is it that she cant hold Meetings in private houses For us and Preach we
                    assign <unclear>this</unclear> as members of the church and witness of Sister
                    Rodeney</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed/>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
